  "abstract": "During the past two decades (1980–2000) donors from developed countries have\r\nbeen promoting structural adjustment in developing countries. This generally includes\r\ngetting the public sector out of an active role in the economy, moving\r\ntoward an open or free-trade regime, and eliminating subsidies (Stiglitz, 2002).\r\nPolicy options, such as marketing boards and input subsidies, have been discouraged,\r\nif not eliminated, as available policy tools at the disposal of most\r\ndeveloping countries......",
